Seems to be understaffed upon entering no reception requesting for service took while for getting the staff attention. However, staff are friendly when attention caught.

Atmosphere: üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
Great space nice and beyond fine dining design.
Abit worry when reading the review but I feel this Tze char has some character.   Not the typical younger serving staff but more like family.   So I totally get it why the bad reviews. ‚Ä¶
I recently decided to give my meat-loving taste buds a break and opt for something fishy instead. So, my family and I made our way to Fish & Co. ‚Ä¶

Amazing food, albeit at a cost. Me and my friends decided to have lunch here on 05072024. The spaghetti bolognese ($10.50) was delicious, although the cheese placement could be changed. The Swedish meatballs (8 pcs for $7.50) were tasty, and the vegetables were well-cooked. The salmon ($11.50) is probably not worth spending on, the amount of fish you get was pitifully small. The cheesecake ($4) was ok for me, although my friends claimed that the berries in the cheesecake were "expired"(?). The crunchy almond chocolate cake ($4) is one to order though, it was delicious. The mashed potatoes were pitifully small (when ordered solo, it cost $1.50). However, the chicken wings ($1 per chicken wing on Fridays) were amazing, although it's probably not a good idea to have this as your main course. The soup that I ordered (add on $2 for a set) was average at best, but the garlic bread saved the day. What was worth it however was the ice cream cone. For $0.50, you get a cone and deliciously cold soya ice cream. The taste of soya was not in the least obvious.

Overall a good meal, although this isn't a place you should come during lunch hour or if you only have a budget of $10 or less.

Value for money for a restaurant in a shopping mall. Ordered Kimchi Dumpling Ramen and Dou Jiang Soup.  Both came with generous portions given the modest price.  In terms of flavor, I'm no South Korean expert, but it taste good enough for me for me to come back.  The restaurant decor is simple and dated, perhaps paying homage to its focus on delivering good food at affordable prices.

Is a quiet estate. My first time there..tried a few dishes with family.  Ordered a chill crab, the meat is fresh,not really my taste, the sauce taste a bit sour,perhaps is thier style lar! Deep fried salmon skin, not worth having, why i ‚Ä¶

(Review for Vegetarians)

Ayasofya is an expensive restaurant just like all restaurants on this very touristy street. So, you not only pay for the good turkish food and the roadside ambience but also for its prime location near the Mosque.

I have tried almost all the Turkish restaurants in this street and elsewhere in Singapore. In my opinion, the food here is good but not too great if you factor in the price. For two persons, for just the vegetarian food shown in the pictures, it was 109.65S$.

The hummus was good but the lavash or balloon bread was too dry and a bit burnt for my taste. They also served falafels that were big and chunky unlike their neighbors on this street that serve coin sized, frozen-falafels. The restaurant opposite to this one, the Sultan Turkish restaurant, has slightly better food but the differences are marginal. But, hands down, the Sultan Turkish restaurant has the better kunefe with goat's milk ice cream.

business_name: Canton Paradise Ê®ÇÂ§©Â∞èÈ¶ôÊ∏Ø at The Star Vista
text:
So busy place and popular meats sold out at night.

Ee mian so nice! But beef kueh tiao meh. The rest not bad.

No more char siew pastry buns, no more char siew at this time

I have very mixed feelings about this place because I've been here twice. The first time we came as a small pax of 2. Service was great and attentive, food excellent and dishes were amazing. However we chose to come here again for a large pax of 8, and booked this way in advance. Staff were inexperienced on the 2nd visit and did not seem knowledgeable on the dishes, and the tables were really not suited for larger pax. This place is not advisable for larger groups. But the food here cannot be faulted.

The best dishes here was the Bossam, Octopus and the bori prawn was addictive. It was well seasoned with chilli powder but not too overpowering. I wasn't a fan of the Tofu kimchi. The servings were meant to be small like tapas, to pair with makgeoli, but the serving size for the Bossam seemed unproportionately too much compared to the other dishes (although I guess usually Bossam has large portions). We sat near the entrance where the atmosphere wasn't that great on both visits, so I'd say best will be to request for a booth seat or a seat further in the next time.

I mean, the restaurant atmosphere and vibes are definitely there. Food is good, but I can't say they're spectacular.
I'm not particularly impressed with the lunch menu. Maybe it's lunch, so the selections are limited.
We were there to celebrate my partner's birthday. The waiters were nice enough to keep our birthday cake in the fridge while we dine.

19th Aug'24
2nd visit almost a year ago.
This time round, seems like the food is tastier.  The clay pot chicken, cereal prawn, curry fish head stands out amongst the other dishes.
Kudos to the waiting staffs who are attentive üëç

25th Aug'23
The salted eggs & chili crabs are good üëç.
For the Assam fish, the flesh is slightly on the tough side.
Oyster omelette quite ok.
Pandan chicken could be better.
Sambal Kang Kong is good.
Cereal prawn is tasty too.

It‚Äôs been a while since I last dined at Monster Curry Jurong Point. They have changed some of their menus. I was surprised to see combination of ebi, tako and omelette rice with the curry. The cost was 14.90SGD. Glad they didn‚Äôt up the price too much. Service was good. The big plates when served were warm. However the ice lemon drink we ordered had too much ice. Hopefully they can cut down on the ice next time.

Food was great! View was also nice for an afternoon visit. Celebrated birthday for a friend and the restaurant offered a plate of complimentary cookies w candle. Alittle costly for 2 course set lunch at $68++ but portion was good for the main. No free coffee for lunch set which was alittle disappointed. Overall was great experience but wasn't perfect.

Food is good. However, the soup we had was ok only. I was expecting really outstanding soup, since this is supposedly a soup specialty resturant.
The san shui chicken is done nicely and the fried mee sua is nice.

Drinks takes quite some time to serve. Felt like they are short of manpower on a Saturday. Food is okay. I‚Äôve eaten worse Collin‚Äôs before. This changes my mind. Pizza soso. Salad could have more veg, it looks really sad.

Fried noodle with chicken taste flavorful.  Signature vermicelli bowl delicious and refreshing.    Weekday mains come with free water/iced viet tea or $5 upgrade to drip coffee and spring roll.  Will try other dishes next visit.  Overall good experience.

Came here on a saturday night with a group of friends for dinner and the restaurant didn't seem too busy. There is a wide variety of food from the Italian cuisine to choose from and pizzas are named after different places in Italy. We started off with truffle fries although could not taste any truffle and they just tasted like plain fries. Garlic bread was good. We ordered three pizzas, one that was gluten free since one of our friends there were gluten free. I had half of the gluten free one although thin crust pizzas are not really my thing and I did not really like the taste. The service was alright although staff did not seem like they knew what they were doing. Overall it was an alright experience but maybe its just because I have never tasted a gluten free pizza before and I am used to the usual pizza taste but my friends really enjoyed their pizzas!

Wow, just wow.
One of the best meals I‚Äôve had in a long time and really appreciate all the thought put into each course. ‚Ä¶

business_name: Boon Lay Traditional Hakka Lui Cha
text:
This stall sells Thunder tea rice/ Lei cha fun.

You have a choice of white or brown rice, and it‚Äôs topped with a medley of diced vegetables (long beans, cabbage, spinach) and beancurd that are stir-fried individually. They also add fried shrimp, which is rather rare for this dish. Peanuts are also added. If you take it away, the peanuts are provided in a separate packet.

The portion is big, good for big eaters or 2 persons

The dish comes with a ‚Äútea‚Äù paste, which is green in color. It‚Äôs a blend of herbs such as mint, coriander, Thai basil and tea leaves, along with an assortment of nuts, such as almond, peanuts and sesame They usually add hot water to it to make a soup. Personally, I prefer to drink it as is, as I can taste the pur√©e by itself.

Try it.

üëçüèªüòã

Japanese Chinese fusion, so if you're after pure authentic Japanese taste, you might be a little disappointed.

Generally, the food are tasty and fresh, no complaints there. Price is very reasonable for the serving and freshness.

To the management, you might also want to reconsider removing the magazines as almost all of them have adult content.

Above average food but quality of sides is meh.

edit 12 july 2025
Came back for the kichi kichi omurice. As expected quality, queue was pretty long tho. the soup given was a standout. also got wasabi as I felt the sauce was too bland. they should give more condiments

Had a meal here on Mother's day. Food was promptly served. Samsui chicken is a must-order dish. Soup of the day (lotus root) and olive rice tasted pretty good to me as well. Tapioca leaves dish was mediocre. ‚Ä¶
Food is good but if you are providing breakfast then at least open by 9 am so people can order in time. They take order only for 10 am which is very late for that.

Reasonably sized tables and chairs, unlike most Japanese restaurants. Food quality was consistent and portions were enough.
Wide variety of food option in their menu.

business_name: The BOILER @ Buona Vista | Best Seafood Boil | Crabs & Lobsters |
text:
Went to have a try with a friend here with no reservations at around 7 which is great. Had the medium duo bag with the sauce of the month. I would say it was pretty dang good though more buns would be great personally the seafood was pretty fresh especially the prawns though I wish it was more generous with the sausages and the corn as there were one piece each. And we ordered the Sri Lanka crab with garlic butter which was a lighter sauce and as well with their promo of 50% off which I don‚Äôt know if they did do the discount on the bill but! It was pretty good. And a little side we ordered was the wings those were honestly great with a nice crunch and to end it off we tried the lava cake which was nice with the side of ice cream as well. No complaints there staff were pretty friendly I would say though they came back twice just to check on the promo they were quite swift as well. Overall ambiance was pretty chill.

Would recommend if craving something unique rather then your normal seafood though quantity I would say could be improved.
Fresh udon - worth to try out. Price is listed as above

Surprisingly decent, the decor and weekend lunch discount (~$20 for a set of appetissr + mains + drinks) made us think it was just an average place but we went in to try all the same and were glad that we tried!

We got the pumpkin risotto and the pork belly, plus crabcake and truffle mushroom soup.
The risotto was actually really refreshing and tasty, while the pork belly wasn't fatty at all and it's honestly the first time I ate something like that, enjoyed the texture.
Overall quite value for money.

Glad that we didn't judge the restaurant from how it looks outside, may come again if in the area.

Visited Leary‚Äôs The Prime Rib, and I have to say the service and atmosphere were absolutely exceptional. From the moment we walked in, the staff made us feel right at home with their warm and attentive hospitality. The ambiance of the restaurant was classic and elegant, perfect for a relaxed yet upscale dining experience.

The spinning salad on ice not bad

For the meal, I started with the mushroom soup and the baby back pork ribs, which were delicious! Tender, flavorful, and cooked to perfection ‚Äì a definite highlight of the evening. However, I was a bit underwhelmed by the signature Lawry‚Äôs Cut Prime. While it was good, I was expecting a bit more flavor and tenderness, especially given the restaurant‚Äôs reputation. It didn‚Äôt quite live up to the hype, but overall, the meal was still enjoyable.

If you're looking for top-notch service and a great atmosphere, Lawry‚Äôs is definitely worth a visit.

Hot Tomato offers great value for the price, especially with their student discounts! The generous portions and tasty dishes make it an excellent choice for a satisfying meal without breaking the bank. It's definitely worth it for the price and flavor!

Dropped by for a quick lunch on a Wednesday afternoon luckily not much of crowd. Quickly placed our orders and the food was served fast. We over ordered for 2 adult n 2 kiddo. End up we have to asked for take away. My kids simply loved the appetiser and we managed to finish 3 plates. Gentleman replaced the appetiser promptly. Food were yummy and pricing is reasonable. Will be back! Thank you
Was delighted by the seamless reservation via Google, and the place was open on a holiday. ‚Ä¶

First thing to say is that Al Amaan has plenty of staff and don‚Äôt seem overloaded with online orders. Was good to see that there are places out west where the customer is valued. The mutton biriyani was decent and good value at 9sg. Shame fish curry had sold out though and tima masala looked like it had gone through some radiation therapy. All in all good value and would probably come back
Nice food
Tasty & Fresh Tasting food, lots of carpark, but out of the way location. You need a car to come here. Above average food prices. Busy at lunch.

Hidden Gem that needs polishing. Tucked in the hidden earths of Singapore, good luck finding this place without a car / grab. But once you reach there, it is a pretty wide space to park your cars for free as it integrates with the plant nursery. We booked and received a booking reservation but upon reaching we‚Äôre told ‚Äúbook on same day no count üòÇ‚Äù, you have to wait like walk in. We visited on a holiday so it was packed during lunch. It took 2 hours to finish our lunch not because we took our time but the mains came late. Apparently only 1 chef on duty today. The quality no doubt is well cooked but our patience wears thin. In addition, as there is no air con seating, you need to battle hard with the flies constantly. Sits possibly 20-25 tables.
Tried the pepper crab, fried rice, salted chicken, and hor fun. The pepper crab was a good. Customer service was average and the outdoor seating near drainage needs improvement. ‚Ä¶
Make your booking with eatigo is good. With max 50% discount (based on timing), pricing of the items are more reasonable. ‚Ä¶

Ordered the prawn aglio olio linguine which was not bad - loved that they were generous with the crunchy prawnsüòç; taste-wise it was quite ok though I personally prefer it to a bit less oily/salty! And if there were more noodles tooüòõ service staff were quite friendly and responsive, as there weren‚Äôt that many diners at that time. ‚Ä¶
This round ordered only 3 dishes and homemade lime juice. Food was good, Kangkong was fresh and soft. Angelica Herbal Roasted Duck was tender. Fish Maw Thick Soup w Black Fungus was nice.

Food is authentic Indian food. Had dum biryani, butter paneer, egg dosai and tissue prata. Price is reasonable.  Prefer this 10x over places like Springleaf prata place.

Update:
Inflation is bad. The serving size is quite small. Lucky to have 5 small cubes of meat in their mutton.
Decent chain steak place. It would he nice if they chilled their canned cokes, but not a big deal. ‚Ä¶

Pleasant experience with high-quality ingredients and good service. Weekend lunch for 2pax after peak hour; the restaurant was quiet and staff were attentive. Starter was hot bread with truffle butter (not pictured); mains were duck confit ‚Ä¶
For the days where you need something quick, healthy & affordable.

Cheerful and helpful staff that assists in ordering. Clean and neat place, surprising large dining area. Both indoor or outdoor dining area options are available. Food variety available at value budget. No extra charge for takeaway, sauces provided. To consider coming back to dine and watch sunset and starry night.

This is a great place to go for Western food. The food quality is pretty good, serving portions are generous, and prices are ok for what you get.
I've enjoyed the steak, grilled and fried chicken, fried fish, calamari and salad. The service is good and staff is efficient. Overall, a nice place to go.

Had dinner here and it can get pretty noisy when crowded. We made a reservation and also stated it‚Äôs for birthday and they gave us a small complimentary cake!

While everything was tasteful, the price was on the high end. It has nice plating but it still doesn‚Äôt cover up for the smaller portion compared to the price. The quality was good but still not super amazing. The lobster bisque doesn‚Äôt actually have dumplings; it‚Äôs just 2 seafood balls made with paste. Truffle fries cant go wrong

The mains were actually served pretty slow (25-30 minutes wait?) yet the servers seemed really quick in wanting to clear out our plates even when we are clearly not finished and still cleaning the last bits of food we have. Had to tell them we were still eating several times when they asked if we wanted to clear. Not sure if it‚Äôs because there is a next reservation, but the food was served slower in the first place ü•≤

The mock tails were good though so you can give it a try for the wide variety they have.

At the start when we got seated down, one of the server asked if we wanted still or sparkling water. We didn‚Äôt know it would be costed ($5 w/o taxes) for a bottle when there is actually refillable tap water available. Just to note for any other future customers getting asked the question ü•π

Would honestly give 3 stars for the food but the good side of the service pulled up the notch to a 4 stars.

Overall it‚Äôs still a welcoming place but it‚Äôs enough to just try once

It‚Äôs been 2nd or 3rd time visiting here. Many customers frequent this food stall at the center; there's often a long queue, but it moves quickly. However, during peak hours, seating can be a challenge, often necessitating sharing tables ‚Ä¶

Decent Vietnamese food with a very nice and chill ambience. Ordered sliced beef pho, BBQ chicken banh mi, and spring rolls (fried and non fried version).
My favourite is probably the pho, but all the food are pretty average overall.
Outdoors is pet-friendly, and the price of the food is pretty value for money, so all in all would recommend if you‚Äôre in the area and looking a pet friendly restaurant.

Ordered the carbonara seafood. Sauce is creamy enough and there is plenty of clams in the pasta dish.

However, the pasta is on the pricier side... After gst, almost all of their pasta dishes will cost more than 22 dollars... i also felt a bit thirsty after eating the food.

Food was good but could be better. One of the dish was too salty. I know the emphasis of the place is the sea salt the place is named after but it was just a little too much. The dish below looks great but the deep fried chicken skin had a taste that didn't blend well with the rest of the dish. Service was also a little patchy. While table service were good and attentive, they were pretty noisy in the background. The restaurant has a fine French restaurant setting. Very lovely but the ambience was marred by sound of cutleries being thrown about in the background like what you get in the kopitiam. I give this place a 4 instead of a 3 because in spite of all these, the food, ambience and service is actually quite good value for money.
Ample portions but not very tasty. Fly flying around
Too bad to have supper night craving. Their staffs are really friendly too.
Nice place for veggie at affordable price.

Came here for the experience of dining in front of the singapore aquarium. The restaurant is small and the staff genuinely attentive and caring, the food is good enough though not exceptional in my view (I wasn‚Äôt disappointed though). My ‚Ä¶

Walked in on Sunday 530pm for early dinner and could get seats readily. What attracted us into the restaurant was the smell, likely from the sizzling hot plates that the steaks are presented on. Had Bacon & Kinoko Hamburg Steak Teishoku. ‚Ä¶

Staff were all very welcoming and attentive. Menu contained mostly of elevated local food fusion with western cuisine. Both Hainanese chicken pasta and Miso salmon chilled soba were quite delicious and generous in portion. Unfortunately, the cappuccino tasted machine made while the muah chee was a little too sweet and lacked the chewiness associated with this snack. Happy Hours from 2-7pm.

business_name: Boon Lay Traditional Hakka Lui Cha
text: First time trying ÊìÇËå∂È•≠. I'm exploring different Hakka dishes. Heard from others that the soup is an acquired taste, I don't see why though. The soup is very flavourful & rich, however I prefer to eat the rice seperately. The crunchy vegetables adds so much texture to the rice, I would like to try the brown rice combination next time! For takeaway, if you like your soup thick, just add less hot water to the ' paste ' given to you. Think matcha lovers would love this too HAHA

I would have to say the food and service are both excellent. The view is a bonus! Had the tasting menu. Everything was excellent
I have to say. Was a little disappointed they didn‚Äôt have omakase menu on the day I came for dinner. I feel they have to at least mention when guests made the bookings. Also, when they served my cocktail, the cocktail glass was chipped, I told the server and he immediately changed a new glass of cocktail, and told me that it would be complementary. This was a nice gesture. But serving cocktails on chipped glasses is definitely not acceptable.

In line with Singapore‚Äôs 60th National Day, elemen's Local‚ÄëLicious 8‚Äëcourse vegetarian set (S$38.80++ for members, $42.80++ otherwise) is a joyous celebration that reimagines our beloved local dishes.

Highlights from the menu:
üá∏üá¨Trio Local Appetiser‚Ä®Delicate char‚ÄØsiew puff, mini roti prata with veggie curry, and chickpea‚Äëtempeh chilli ‚Äúcrab‚Äù‚ÄØ‚Äî‚ÄØa clever, colourful starter that winks at hawker classics.
üá∏üá¨ Salad Flatbread Rolls with Indian Rojak Dressing‚Ä®Crisp greens and fruit rolled in soft flatbread, drizzled with zesty assam‚Äëinfused Indian rojak sauce‚Äîbright, tangy and refreshingly fun.
üá∏üá¨ Peppery ‚ÄúFish Maw‚Äù Soup‚Ä®Vegetarian ‚Äúfish maw‚Äù with king oyster mushrooms, goji, red date broth, topped with crispy soy croutons‚Äîcomforting, earthy, and subtly peppery.
üá∏üá¨ Lion‚Äôs Mane Satay‚Ä®Meaty lion‚Äôs mane mushrooms grilled, served with satay sauce and ketupat‚Äîsatisfyingly charred and hearty, evoking classic street‚Äëside skewers.
üá∏üá¨ Black Truffle Hainanese ‚ÄúChicken‚Äù Rice‚Ä®Star of the menu - truffle‚Äëinfused rice with plant‚Äëbased ‚Äúchicken‚Äù. It‚Äôs luxe yet familiar‚Äîa surprising twist on SG staple.
üá∏üá¨ Coconut Chendol Beancurd Pudding‚Ä®Creamy coconut pudding, pandan chendol, red beans, gula melaka‚Äîsweet, nostalgic, and silky.
üá∏üá¨ Radiance in a Cup‚Ä®Snow‚Äëgum and red date drink to round off‚Äîlight and refreshing with a ‚Äúnest‚Äëlike‚Äù nourishing feel.

elemen‚Äôs Local‚ÄëLicious 8‚ÄëCourse Menu delivers a seamless blend of creativity, nostalgia and value. Each dish cleverly reinterprets cherished local flavours in a meat-free way, paying homage to Singapore‚Äôs culinary heritage with elegance and flair.

My family and I visited Brio for the first time with 7 pax. Right off the bat, the staff were friendly enough to cater a big table for us despite having no reservation with a full house as well. I rate this review with a 3 star service mainly because we had to return 2 dishes as it was not ours. The atmosphere was nonetheless pretty cool, food was delicious but not overly exciting.

Pizza 3/5 üåü
Burgers 6/5 üåü (Very juicy A+)
Calamari 4/5 üåü
Pastas 4/5 üåü
Tater Tots 5/5 üåü(Can't go wrong)
Milkshakes 6/5 üåü
Had the beef and pork set, quite nice. Also ordered Kimchi Pancake, Tteokbokki and steam egg. Side dishes and sauces are free flow.

We got the sharing set for 2 which cost $55 per pax. It came with kimchi platter which had 7 different kimchis and we enjoyed them. Makgeolli steamed bun which was so good and soft, and pairs well with the black sauce. ‚Ä¶

It was a good and satisfying meal!

The food was flavourful and saucy.   The portions were decent for the price.  It ‚Ä¶

Menu variety is good
Price reasonable
Food is delicious
Wonderful sea view of Johor Straits
Worth the travel time

This is one of the places that i would visit if i were to bring my dog out with me for dinner. They are pet friendly.  We ordered a salad and mushroom soup for starter and taco and pan fry fish as main. The soup is thick and smooth while the salad ia crunchy.
We love how simple the fish is pan fried. Taco is really tasty too. But most importantly, the music wasnt too loud and that my dog clould sit close to us feeling relaxed.

The number of dishes on offer at this eatery is mind blowing! We ordered the Mee Goreng Pattaya (meat free) for myself, Tulang Soup for my dad and Butter Chicken w Rumali Roti for my mum. All the dishes were tasty, and reasonably priced. ‚Ä¶

A solid favorite in Jurong Point: Sai Kitchen. Their vegetarian thali offers a great variety of dishes‚Äîdal, paneer, curry, rice, roti, chutney‚Äîeach well‚Äëseasoned and satisfying. Service is efficient, and portions are generous. The restaurant is clean and welcoming, and ideal for families or solo diners. If you're craving a wholesome Indian meal in Jurong, this one‚Äôs hard to beat.

Great food at a nice location by the river . The chef actually stepped out and enquired about our meal which was excellent.
The waitstaff pretty much left us alone after serving  the meal initially and ‚Ä¶

love the pizza and pastas here but the real star of our meal was definitely the tuna tartare. service was a little slow because we were seated on the 2nd floor so maybe ask to be seated downstairs instead ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è ‚Ä¶

How to get the promo:
Order the $48 fish. Only that one has 58% off, only when you pay the bill at cashier then you will see it reflected.
I liked the cauliflower. The ÂÜ∞Á≤â dessert is too big for 2.
I queued for 1hr 15min.

$36 for rice, fish and pork, and 60 cents laziji.

Great to see a subway cafe located in Tuas South. It is only open in weekdays and a bit quite as it is located in Industrial area. Quite ulu and not well-served by public bus. Overall the service is good.

I have the same feeling I had eight years ago .. on the pallet... Spot on... Wish i could have that dessert she made in masterchef guest appearance !!! Evelyn thanks for your hospitality.. good job..
Keep it up...  Ms wong

This is the spot for value for money bbq seafood! We ordered sambal stingray, sambal sotong and petai!

All super flavourful with that smokiness and just the right amount of spice. (It does get salty over time so best to pair it with a bowl of rice) Stingray was fresh and meaty, sotong was nice and tender (not super chewy), and the petai was tasty and crunchy, the way I love it.

For this meal, 2pax spent less than $40 for these.

Great place for bbq seafood cravings! C e early! Oh and they accept cdc vouchers! :)

We visited the restaurant during lunch hours and were greeted warmly and seated outdoors as we had not made a reservation. Despite the warm weather, the fan and portable air conditioner provided some relief, though there were a few flies ‚Ä¶

business_name: Sen Sen Sushi Jem by DON DON DONKI Singapore
text:
The food was great, but the experience wasn't the best. We were seated at the corner of the rows of seats. Unfortunately, the corner is where the dirty plates wheeled collector being placed. This undermined the whole experience as the smell was a bit offputting.

Service was all right.

I've tried this store multiple times for lunch, sampling various dishes from chicken and mutton to beef rendang. Today, I ordered the beef rendang, while my colleague opted for the chicken rendang. The set came with two side dishes, ‚Ä¶

Been there with colleagues as a team bonding session. Food was pretty good and we enjoyed it. Some of the minus points are they don't serve fresh juice with no added sugar and there were flies flying around in such a atas restaurant.

The Estate @Hilton Orchard
The hotel breakfast was great, and the service staff was very attentive. I really enjoyed the local flavor buffet spread. The only downside was that the air conditioning vent was directly overhead, which wasn‚Äôt very comfortable. Other than that, everything was excellent.

One of the more popular chicken rice stall in this region. Expect queue, from start till food runs out. Rice by itself is good enough for me to eat on itself. Chicken is soft and tender, added some char siew for taste of pork. Can taste hint of vinegar, ginger and garlic in the chili. Soup provided. Overall good combo, good value on price/portion. Heard they provide child portion too.

Excellent service by the staff! Very friendly and helpful. We had the birthday menu set, which was very worth it! Received an amazing platter of fruits that was complimentary and on the house for our birthday celebration!

Interesting place. The deep fried chicken was a bit too tough to bite (personal).  Set comes with mineral water, a small (glutinous rice lookalike) waffle & a fruit.  The soup and pork was nice.

Paid $18.90 nett for the set, felt a tad on higher side.  Overall food was ok.  Outside seating is nice and airy.

There is parking at the basement of the CC.
Good only for the Giant supermarket and maybe the gym. The foodcourt has your typical food average taste nothing fantastic, pricing is considered not too expensive or cheap.

Slightly disappointed, it was very pricey and also AC was freezing cold!
Food and ambiance overall was good, we had the signature black cod , the beef was also great but the rest was soso. A plus was the service which was quite ‚Ä¶

Actually pretty decent food here. The family enjoyed everything we ordered especially the deep fried shrimps and cauliflower. They go very well with their citrus mayo dip, so highly recommended. I had the barbeque bacon burger and that ‚Ä¶

Overall foods are goods.
The mushrooms rice is superb, over salmon rice.
The seafoods spaghetti is excellent. But the tomyam noodle is a bit mild, should put more paste.
The pork ribs is also a must...
The share platters are very very good if U are having gatherings with friends or relatives.....
The foods portion is relatives smaller. But this is what camping foods all about.....üò¨ü§≠

Went on a weekday, place is cosy and nice, away from the city area.

Service was good. ‚Ä¶

Their menu has changed since the day I frequented their Bedok branch. Still undergoing menu change, not all items are available. Check with staffs.
Truffle fries to start our meal was a great choice‚Ä¶ crunchy and not overly oily.
Carbonara was average though‚Ä¶ a little watery and lacking a few more pieces of bacon bits.
Cajun chicken thigh (new item) with silky smooth mashed potato and rice was a great combination.
Ribeye steak not the best cut, a little chewy.
Latte very well made.

Genki sushi has always been my family's to go sushi place as my kids loved the sight of the train delivering the sushi. After visiting this place, I'm beginning to think that this may be our new hangout.

I really like the variety and uniqueness of the sushi they serve here. The especially like the thick cut salmon sashimi that is so satisfying to chew on. Food arrives promptly after ordering. Do come earlier as the queue forms rather quickly.
Upscale Szechuan cuisine with dum sum. Limited selection dum dum. If you are looking for traditional dum sum this is not for you. No BBQ pork and roast duck. Peking duck is on offer. Busy place.
I wish you a merry Christmas

business_name: Red Lantern Live Seafood @ 921 Upper Bukit Timah Road
text:
Brought my family there for weekend dinner.
Main gripe is that we wanted to order Curry Fish Head or Steamboat Fish Head ($38), but was told that both were sold out and the only fish left is the seasonal fish ($48). We got that in the end which was pretty large with much meat, just that I don‚Äôt know if the reason above is a smokescreen for us to spend more‚Ä¶

Anyway the Fingertips Chicken was amazing as the meat while tender, contained so much flavor from the spices used, so I was impressed how the chef infused the spices into the meat. The rest were decent too.

Free parking available at the building but limited lots, otherwise a lot of cars park along side the small road of the building. Last resort is to park at Hilton Mall then cross the street to the restaurant.
Tasty but not the place to go to if you're looking for grilled

Good Food, but More South Indian Vibes

I tried two North Indian thalis and a masala dosa at Nalan Singapore. The food ‚Ä¶

Went with family of 7 on 4 may 2025. Teriyaki chicken burger was simply succulent. Sirloin medium rare was just nice and fresh. Kids‚Äô free meals like pepperoni pizza and prawn spaghetti were satisfactory. Family enjoyed the dinner & Will patronise again.

Simple and straightforward Chinese cuisine situated at level 2 of Raffles Marina Country club. The Bistro at level 1 gets most attention but the food here is definitely worth a try. Their 4pax 5 course set menu is about $69.90++ - comes with decent portion and includes soup and dessert. The mango pudding dessert is exceptional! Service is also very satisfactory. Thank you, team!

Overall, the food was good, except for the grilled chicken, which ended up being dry and deep-fried. When I asked the staff, they explained that the chicken is first grilled and then deep-fried to shorten the waiting time, as some customers had previously complained about delays.

Redeemed the Gyoza & Udon after accumulation of stamps on the e rewards card. You are also able to browse the menu on RE&S website. Tried the crispy pork, it was ok. Food here is average as always with its reasonable price. The service here is much better than JP branch.

We were nearby so we wanted to have vegetarian food for lunch. The restaurant is situated at the Nanyang Community Club. It‚Äôs a nice decorated restaurant and it‚Äôs not crowded either, no reservation is required. There is a wide variety choices in the menu. I ordered the claypot rice. Surprisingly it taste good and food is flavorful. It exceeded my expectation. Service is good, waiting time for food is average 5min to 10min. I would definitely be back again. Looking forward to try other dishes.

Nice authentic Mexican food and the best for sharing with bunch of friends. The ambience was good especially during festive season. To be honest, didn‚Äôt know what to order. Just ask the waiters for the recommendation. Overall the food was good and staff were attentive. We booked table at 6pm and we must leave by 8pm. There is a car park space behind Margarita (in case full in front of Margarita).

business_name: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine ÊπòÈ¶ôÊπñÂçóËèú @ Jurong Point
text:
Tried their food during 40%off. We told them less oil, less salt and less spicy. Surprised the taste  just right for us except the olive green bean became of the preserved olive veg abit salty. I think without it will taste better.
The stir-fried Angus beef is super delicious with lot of big pieces of garlic.
The Saucer fish in golden soup, slice fish is thin but still in whole piece. I expected the soup more sour. Overall the soup bring out the tangy, savory delight that's sure to tantalize your taste buds.

Wonderful dining place with nice ambience. Food was nice. Unfortunately our servers attitude was not great. Politely requested for correct wine glasses to be used and she initially refused. Subsequently raised her voice at us and insisted we should have informed her beforehand.

The fusion pastas, Hae Bi Hiam Linguine and Chilli Crab Tagliatelle, captured the essence of our local flavours with their spice and umami-laden gravy. Would have been even better if they had used fresh prawns in the former.
Interestingly, their rendition of the Ayam Penyet Briyani comes with cous cous (with an option to change to white rice), cucumber, sambal, taukwa and pickled veg. Parts of the chicken were pretty dry though.

For indoor dining, each diner is required to order 1 crepe. If there are 3 pax, it is required to order 3 crepe. Having said that, their Crepe were flavourful. And perhaps outdoor dining for next visit‚Ä¶
This little eatery nested beneath the Pandan Valley condo brings out the uniqueness of French cuisine. ‚Ä¶

Great ramen fix in a place where food options are generally lacking!

The broths are rich and wholesome, collar chashu very tenderly done, belly ‚Ä¶

Been wanting to try this restaurant for a while and finally got the chance! Loved that they offer Peking duck alongside their signature fish ‚Äî a nice variety on the menu. Visited on a weekday in the late afternoon, and it was pretty quiet, which made for a relaxing dining experience. The flower tea was a lovely touch too ‚Äî light and refreshing, great for balancing out the richness of the meal. Overall, no complaints ‚Äî a hearty and satisfying meal!

Cozy environment and Japanese authentic tasting meals! Friendly staff who is helpful with recommendations. Highly recommend to have a drink or two to go with the food for a great immersive experience!

Under Der Linden restaurant offers a pleasant dining environment with beautiful decor that sets a charming ambiance. However, the menu options are quite limited, with only three types of desserts available. Additionally, the service is a ‚Ä¶

business_name: Shan Cheng (Ipoh Delicacies) ‚óè Â±±Âüé - Bukit Panjang Plaza
text:
Legend has it that the food here is so good that a tycoon flew a helicopter to Ipoh just to get a taste! Hence, the name Helicopter Rice ($10.80). Flooded with three kinds of curry, it is both aromatic and very spicy.

Ipoh Chicken Hor fun ($8.80) comes in both soup and dry versions. Paired with prawns and chives (prawns a bit overcooked).

A must-try for people who love fried food is the Golden Platter ($9 small, $14.90 large). Everything is made in Ipoh except for the fishballs. The turnip in the middle is naturally sweet, no condiments needed.

For drinks, don‚Äôt leave without their White Coffee ($2.60 hot, $3.30 cold) or Milk Tea Latte ($4.80). I swear, the tea is so fragrant, with a frothy creamy top.

Grab some traditional pastries to go! So many choices from Meat Floss with Lotus Paste Biscuit to Heong Pheah. They also have a unique egg tart with a pineapple centre!
Just stick to the beverages, bread and half boiled eggs.
Nice setting in the private room looking over MBS. Food was delicious. Service good. Very enjoyable evening.

Overall, the food was not bad. The waffles are nice, just the fried chicken that comes with it was over fried (too dry). Environment is ok, and suggestion is to make reservations before coming if you don't want to wait.

Very nice place to relax and rest after walking the park, coupled with superb views by the window seats. AMAZING service by our waiter, Syah, too! Food was abit ex for the portion sizes, but its sg so everything is ex‚Ä¶

Oh, rmb to ask for pepper and ull be in for a surprise haha :)
Though looks a bit rundown passing through the passage of time, it's still one of the best restaurants in this area. The scintillating sushi emits an alluring temptation.

business_name: PastaMania ‚Äì Italian Casual Dining @ West Mall
text: The chicken basil pizza n banana brownie are nice but not the honey chicken and carbonara. Students meal not in online ordering system so didn‚Äôt manage to order that for my 2 kids üòì ‚Ä¶

A contemporary Italian restaurant located within the heart of Orchard. Made a reservation for our anniversary dinner on a weekday night and the restaurant was pleasantly quiet.

We had the 5-course set dinner with the choice to top up for pastas and mains. I had the white truffle pasta and steak  while the hubby had the squid ink pasta and pigeon.

It was interesting how they presented the white truffle in a wooden box and shaved the truffle right on my pasta.

The staff were friendly and offered to take photos for us for the special occasion. Overall a pleasant dining experience.

Simple and lovely northern Indian meals. We had the plain briyani which was vibrant, fragrant and soft. The mutton vindaloo was tender and spicy hot! The mushroom and peas were delicious though hubby thought it was slightly sweet but hey, maybe it‚Äôs the way it‚Äôs supposed to be. We didn‚Äôt have bread as the rice was just enough for two. The pistachio kulfi was yummy! Not too sweet but I wish there was more pistachio bits. Will be back to try other dishes!

Food was good and service was prompt. The place was not too noisy unlike some Chinese restaurants. Dumpling soup is clear and taste very fresh. Their signature beehoon is very good. Chilli clams was a little disappointing but overall the food was still very good.

The staff are warm and helpful. And the food is actually really great. Only one thing, though...all the dishes were really very salty. I'm not sure if that's just how this cuisine is, apologies, but it is really super salty.

My friend had made a booking under a name I wasn't aware of, and I'd arrived earlier. The Filipino service guy simply dismissed me and said "maybe you don't have a booking then" but thankfully I spotted my friend's number on his screen. ‚Ä¶

business_name: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine ÊπòÈ¶ôÊπñÂçóËèú @ Jurong Point
text: They have free ice cream. Food is tasty and portions are huge for 1 person. The chef have exceptional knife skills as the meat slices are deftly cut into bite sizes. I did order 2 more dishes, the suan cai fish and steam egg with prawns as I was hungry for more.

text: Kimchi soup tastes good. If the bulgogi could be changed to a hotpot sliced, it would be great. According to the restaurant policy, each person needs to order one meal. A Deliciously Flaky Experience at Niqqi's The Cheese Prata Shop, Clementi*

Tucked away in the bustling neighborhood of Clementi, Niqqi's The Cheese Prata Shop is a hidden gem that has been tantalizing taste buds with its delectable cheese pratas. As a self-proclaimed prata enthusiast, I was excited to try their signature dish and see if it lives up to the hype.

Upon entering the shop, I was greeted by the friendly staff and the aroma of freshly baked prata. The menu boasted an impressive array of prata options, but I stuck to the classic cheese prata. The verdict? Absolutely delightful!

The cheese prata was cooked to perfection, with a crispy, flaky crust giving way to a gooey, cheesy center. The cheese was generously portioned, and the prata itself was cooked just right ‚Äì not too oily, not too dry. Each bite was a masterful balance of flavors and textures that left me craving for more.

What sets Niqqi's apart from other prata shops is the attention to detail and commitment to quality. The ingredients are fresh, and the cooking technique is evident in every bite. The shop's cozy atmosphere and friendly service only add to the overall experience.

While the cheese prata is undoubtedly the star of the show, I also tried their egg prata, which was equally impressive. The egg was cooked just right, with a runny yolk that added a rich, creamy texture to the dish.

In conclusion, Niqqi's The Cheese Prata Shop is a must-visit destination for anyone who loves good food and great company. With its mouth-watering cheese pratas and welcoming atmosphere, this shop is sure to become a favorite among locals and visitors alike. Whether you're a prata aficionado or just looking for a delicious meal, Niqqi's is definitely worth a try.

Rating: 4.5/5 stars

Price: Affordable ($5-$7 per prata)

Recommended for: Prata enthusiasts, foodies, and anyone looking for a tasty meal

I'm already planning my next visit to try more of their prata options.

Overall a lovely experience and service. They have good promos for beers too if you are keen. Parking is free but of course getting here is most convenient by car. Ambience is quiet and cosy enough for an enjoyable meal. Pets are welcomed too at the alfresco seating area.

Dining at Odette was nothing short of extraordinary. From the moment we arrived, we were welcomed with such warmth and attentiveness that it felt less like being treated as royalty, and more like being truly honoured guests ‚Äî graciously and thoughtfully looked after from start to finish.

The 7-course d√©gustation was divine. Each dish was a delicate balance of flavour, technique, and creativity ‚Äî and the way the food was presented felt almost like a performance. There was a sense of quiet theatre in the room, with fellow diners visibly in awe as each course arrived. It was beautiful to witness ‚Äî a shared appreciation for artistry on the plate.

The mushroom soup was a comforting and elegant standout, while the dumpling and the egg dish showcased incredible finesse. And surprisingly, the pigeon ‚Äî something I wouldn‚Äôt normally gravitate toward ‚Äî was absolutely delicious, prepared to perfection.

Their beverage selection was extensive and thoughtfully curated, perfectly complementing the meal. And the service? Flawless. Every interaction felt genuine, knowledgeable, and perfectly timed.

If you have the time, I can‚Äôt recommend the full experience highly enough ‚Äî especially with the added touches and optional extras. Odette isn‚Äôt just a restaurant. It‚Äôs a celebration of food, beauty, and hospitality at its finest.

One of the best buffet quality I've had in a long time. Had the semi buffet on valentines day with my wife and this is basically a salad bar buffet for $58/pax, and you can add on an entree for an extra $10. They also had wines for $14/glass, but this was only limited to a specific red and white wine. The buffet spread isn't very wide, but the quality was fantastic. Almost everything was a hit. Other tab the cold cuts and salads, there was also basis breads, a cheese station, and desserts. I especially enjoyed the soup of the day, which was a corn and crab soup - something I would not order normally and was actually disappointed in hearing about, but when it came and I tried it, I changed my mind immediately - it was that good. One Ninety, if you're reading this, you need to put this soup in your regular menu rather than have it as soup if the day.

For the entrees, I had the salmon and my wife had the duck leg, and both were very solid. The duck leg came with a sauce that tastes like Peking duck sauce, very creative and the meat was fall if the bone. The salmon came with an unknown sauce that looks a bit like pesto or chimichuri,but want very tasty. Nevertheless the salmon was fresh and succulent and cooked perfectly.

Dessert selection wasn't very wide either, but several of them were good. The $14 wines however didn't tickle our fancy, so we got the regular wines, which was very good. Comes with coffee or tea at the end too. I had a caf√© latte while my wife had a decaf caf√© latte. Both were unexpectedly good for a hotel buffet. In fact better than many cafes. Total came up to about $250 for 2 pax.

Service was excellent - professional, polite, earnest, but not overbearing. Pretty much the gold standard. Even the junior waiters seemed properly trained.

Would definitely come again for special occasions.

In Singapore, there‚Äôs a land scarcity as so many are used to build buildings. It‚Äôs so refreshing to see a farm in our very own Singapore where it‚Äôs as authentic and rural as it can be. If you‚Äôre looking to clear your mind, or just take in the wonderful nature, this is the place to go!

It has been my long-running wish to dine at Candlenut. Rather than feeling exquisitely modern like typical Michelin restaurants, Peranakan cuisine is typically cooked with thoughtful preparation and tastes like how your grandma(in SEA) would cook! Like most Asian cultures, it is best in a group of 4-5 so you can order multiple dishes a la carte. For couples, there‚Äôs still the ah-ma-kase!

Chef‚Äôs Mum‚Äôs Chicken Curry
One of the signature items in Candlenut, the curry is on the sweeter end and is very ‚Äòlemak‚Äô (aromatic) from the coconut milk. The chicken is not fall-off-the-bone but retains its texture while being easy peel off the bone. Get this with white rice!

Candlenut Buah Keluak Fried Rice
A must order signature dish! Buah Keluak is a nut that gives the fried rice a nutty profile (obviously). It is slightly spiced and has a surprisingly good wok hey to it. Make sure to break the yolk to give it an extra creaminess.

Cassava Kueh
Never ever skip dessert at Candlenut. Other than the signature Chendol, this kueh was really mind blowing. It‚Äôs a kueh(cake) uses grated tapioca base, topped with a custard layer that is wonderfully brulee - giving it a flan-like flavour. Make sure to have scoops of the Gula Melaka sorbet in between!

text: It‚Äôs been a while we last visited this restaurant. The food is still as good and the service is still great. Always enjoy the beef tenderloin with many fresh herbs. If you‚Äôre around this area, this is the place for a nice dinner.

Stepping into Cherki, you‚Äôre immediately greeted by a bold teal backdrop and a touch of Peranakan elegance ‚Äî perfectly setting the tone for the meal ahead. The lunch set comes beautifully served in intricate, floral-patterned tiffin carriers, making the experience feel both nostalgic and luxurious.

The star of the presentation is the blue pea flower rice, its vibrant hue naturally derived and paired with a medley of aromatic dishes. Each compartment holds a well-balanced variety ‚Äî from tender, flavorful meat dishes to rich, fragrant curries, accompanied by crunchy pickles and crispy crackers for texture contrast.

Every bite offers layers of flavor: the tangy-sweet sambal, the earthy spices of slow-cooked meat, and the gentle coconut aroma of the rice all harmonize beautifully. The meal is thoughtfully portioned ‚Äî hearty enough to satisfy, but light enough to leave you comfortably full.

To wash it down, the drinks selection ranges from refreshing citrus-based coolers to aromatic teas, each complementing the richness of the meal. Presentation is top-notch; the combination of Peranakan artistry and modern plating elevates the dining experience beyond just taste.

business_name: Dim Sum Express (Kuai Can Dian Xin)
text:
A great place for a quick dim sum bite at a really affordable price. The variety available here is impressive, with many selections to choose from ranging from the usual classics like siew mai, har gow, char siew bao, and chee cheong fun, to other tasty small plates that make it easy to order a spread for sharing. Every dish I tried was tasty and freshly prepared, with quality comparable to what you would expect at other dim sum shops. Portion sizes are also reasonable and consistent with typical dim sum standards, so you can order a good mix without feeling that the servings are too small.

What makes this spot even better is that it‚Äôs housed within a coffee shop that also offers plenty of other food choices. This makes it very convenient if you are visiting with friends or family who might prefer different dishes beyond dim sum. You can easily mix and match, sharing plates from the dim sum stall alongside noodles, rice, or other hawker favourites available within the same space. It really adds to the overall dining experience and makes it suitable for groups of all ages.

The atmosphere is casual and unpretentious, perfect for a fuss-free meal. Service is quick, and food is served hot, so it‚Äôs ideal if you‚Äôre in the area and just want a satisfying meal without waiting too long. Parking is also not an issue here‚Äîthe carpark is located just beside the coffee shop with plenty of available lots. The rates are affordable compared to other busy areas, which makes it even more convenient for those driving.

Overall, this is a reliable and budget-friendly choice for dim sum lovers looking for good variety, value for money, and easy accessibility.

Just a short 5 mins walk from the Buona Vista MRT lies this unassuming restaurant filled with friendly service and delicious food. We really enjoyed the Jalapeno in Tostada, beef cheek and lamb shank. As many reviewers mentioned, the beef cheek and lamb shank are so tender and soft (not forgetting flavourful!). Even the accompanying vegetables on the main dishes are cooked perfectly. Great happy hour deals (8++ for house wine and beer) and even happier when paired with grab dine out deals.

Great place if for a nice evening where you can enjoy food which would have cost at least 2.5 times more in town. The Tomahawk is a must-try but do pre-book when making your reservation. The owner, Desmond will go out of his way to enhance your experience.

Tried the set meal. Happy, good food good value.
The tomahawk steak is awesome as well.

I've always had positive experiences at Toast Box in West Coast Plaza. They consistently maintain the richness and quality of coffee, and the black sesame spread toast has never let me down.
I found that both Toast Box at Jem and Jurong Point , erm....The black sesame spread is extremely scarce and applied very thinly, which left me feeling quite disappointed.
Consistent good quality for food. Great option for Japanese food in this area . I must have visited it 10 times in last 12 months

business_name: Indian Muslim / Halal food - Vellimani Restaurant Pte Ltd
text: Delicious

This is a top notch dining place. The food was superb. We had the signature mushroom soup, grilled lamb, grilled prawns, grilled cauliflower and also mushrooms for sides. The service was great. The team checked in with us if we were enjoying the food, if we have suggestions for improvements, and before we asked; staff stepped in to volunteer to help us take photos. Upon knowing it was my friend‚Äôs birthday, they served a slice of tiramisu cake on the house. Will definitely return even though the location is quite out of the way. But the experience really calls for a second visit. Keep up the awesome service!!!!
The food was excellent every dish was well-executed with distinct layers of texture and flavour. Service was good too, as expected from a restaurant of this calibre. ‚Ä¶

You know the saying ‚Äî if a restaurant looks nice, the food might not be good? Well, Cavern Restaurant completely breaks that myth. The place has a fantastic ambience, really unique and cozy, making the whole dining experience special. ‚Ä¶

Great food, but would like to highlight one thing for the sake of the staff members.

There is a very sweet older lady, and we appreciate her attentiveness to her customers. She asked us how the food was, and even gave us a takeaway box with extra plastic bag when we asked for just the box to takeaway. For employer reference, it was the attendant on the floor on 8th of August during my time sitting from 12:45pm to 1:30pm.

Separately however, because of the 60 cent wing promotion, I felt that there were a few things that went wrong with the queueing system because of the large crowd. Upon arriving, we noted that there was the sign that said to get a seat inside before also queueing for the food. Hence my family members got a seat closer to when we were approaching the cashier. We were directed by a ‚Äúfrantic‚Äù staff member who told us to stay in the ‚Äúhaving here‚Äù queue. However, when we were second from the cashier, she told us we queued up wrongly and would have to go to the back of the line because we were in the ‚Äúseat‚Äù queue instead of the ‚Äúfood‚Äù queue. I‚Äôve been queuing for about 20 minutes, and being asked to queue at the back of the line after being misdirected by the same staff herself was very off-putting. Also, she kept jabbing and tapping my arm the entire time she was asking me to go to the back of the line‚Ä¶. Not cool please. I‚Äôm hoping it never happens to me again as a regular customer of jinjja. Thankfully (also i guess she didn‚Äôt wanna escalate the situation) she opened up her cashier to rectify and de-escalate.

My 5 stars comes from a place of love for the food and experience crafted by some of the staff members. But i do wish that the issues i‚Äôve addressed in this review can be taken seriously by upper management. Please do not put your staff in the situation where they are stressed out by the sudden promotion and crowd, and designate proper signage to help both your customers and staff. Thanks!

Went there for lunch with parents and sibling. These people are hardcore Chinese foodies. So when I suggested this French place, they really gave me that doubtful look. Parking is a breeze (weekday) and I got the nearest lot to the restaurant.

Went in and was greeted by the handsome chef and his partner. Brought us to our table and we starting looking at the menu. We ordered the set menu which was a really good deal in my opinion. The food came after a while and we started pecking.

The fish was my favorite, outside is crispy with a moist inside. Mash and veg was also spot on 9/10. Beef stew which we topped up for the dish was under seasoned. After adding more salt it became very delightful. Meat is soft and tender, mash and veg spot on as well 7.5/10. Chicken dish is also very good (round shaped) it came with a sauce that compliment it very well 7.5/10. Desert is okay, nothing much to brag about 6/10. At the end of the meal, everyone was happy and satisfied. Overall it‚Äôs a gem and value for money 8/10. Will be back for more.

We ordered the curry fish head and rojak - excellent. Most customers there were eating the char kway teow. We were offered the desserts a few times, but were too full to indulge. This place is popular, and I can see why

This place is super fun. Be sure to choose two hours. It is recommended to keep things in lockers, where there is no place to store. It's not allowed to bring photo equipment, which is a little disappointment. This place is suitable for team building and friends. If you want to have fun, don't wear socks and gloves. If you don't want to fall into the water, it is recommended to wear gloves and non-slip socks.

Loved the food selection at Colony! The ambience is very relaxing for buffet-style dining. The food and service were both excellent‚Äîspecial thanks to Edward and Rahul! They even gave our kids coloring materials to keep them entertained while we enjoyed our meal.

We'll definitely be back!

Great food quality, wonderful atmosphere. I tried pork loin today as main course, it was tender and so satisfactory. But what I loved the most among all good ingredients and presentation was perfectly cooked Japanese rice. It‚Äôs simple yet so important for Japanese cuisine. I couldn‚Äôt love it more and will return!

We came here to celebrate my sister‚Äôs birthday, and everything exceeded our expectations. The service was exceptional‚ÄîMega and the other waiters were incredibly attentive and gave fantastic recommendations that did not disappoint. The food was delicious, and we barely had to wait for it to arrive, which made the whole evening even more enjoyable. From start to finish, it was a memorable dining experience. Highly recommend!

What an Unexpected Hidden Gem of a place in Little India! I just celebrated my birthday at this lovely cosy restaurant! To begin with, the place feels like my own private dining space as max capacity is 12 to 13 pax. For the food, I love the Creamy Ravioli, Duck Confit, Foie Gras and the Creme Brulee! I also love the escargots and fish dishes too! The Lady Chef is friendly and does the cooking and serving! The food is simply delicious! I will certainly return again with my friends! What a Unique and lovely dining experience!
Amazing air conditioned environment, nasi lemak taste authentic

business_name: Red Lantern Live Seafood @ 921 Upper Bukit Timah Road
text: Staffs are very friendly and they do appreciate return customers like us‚Ä¶ music sound system is nice and they don‚Äôt rush you to finish your food.. nice and yummy appetiser side dishes as well! Experienced chefs cooking, you can taste from the food.. no disappointment whenever we try different dishes..

After the wonderful and memorable lunch I had at Braci many years ago, I have been thinking of going back again. And the International Women‚Äôs Day Special at Braci gave me the exact motivation to push aside all my commitments, prior plans and beauty appointment to come here to enjoy these specially curated dishes, with southeast Asian influences, created by the female chefs at Braci. This is one of the best dining experiences I have.

Instead of serving pure Italian food for the special occasion, the dishes in the menu feature European cuisine with Southeast Asian influences, inspired by the chefs‚Äô backgrounds. I totally love it. There are so many flavours packed in beautiful harmony within each dish, It is complex and spellbinding.

I opt to dien at the exciting rooftop bar with a quaint bar counter and 270 ¬∞ panoramic unblocked view of the Singapore River, the landscape of Marina Bay and skyline of the city. It is so breathtaking, and the soft breeze blowing makes it even better Yes, I feel like I‚Äôm living it up when dining here.

The service is exceptional, impeccable and friendly, completing the exceptional experience of savouring awesome food with awesome ambience and service.

Makan Makan by Chef Li Vian is a lovely trio of Tom Kha Kai, Corn Tarlet and Scallop Semifreddo. I love the transition from simulating taste of Tom Kha Kai to smokiness of Corn Tarlet, and finally to luxurious treat of Scallop Semifreddo.

Suan Ni Bai Rou by Chef Aaron is one of the best pork dish I have. With the pork belly soaked with wine, sprinkled with fried shallots, paired with umami rich Sakura Ebi Furikake and zesty cool Cucumber Snow, the medley of rich flavours is amazing.

Aglio&Olio, But I don't like Garlic is very interestingly named by its creater, Chef Yoke. Given a twist to Braci's signature 32 Egg Yolks Tagliolini with creamy sweet Bafun Uni, which is by the way the best pasta, garlic foam and hamaguri clams are added for the extra oomph in taste and crunchy texture. The Tagliolini here is a must-try.

Tropical Tart by Pastry Chef Yasmin is a delightful dessert made up of mango mousse, passion fruit and coconut sorbet. Full of nuanced flavours, it tastes refreshing and rich at the same time. I love it.

Thoughts: Amazing Beautiful Experience that hits all the Sweet Spots

With my husband I spent a lovely evening at Nox. From the welcoming till the goodbye everything was wonderful.
We started with their signature cocktails/mocktails, absorbed the atmosphere and ‚Ä¶

Prepare your taste buds for a gourmet journey unlike any other at Singapore's Xi Yan Seafood Restaurant. This acclaimed restaurant serves a feast of delicious tastes and well cooked seafood dishes that will leave you wanting more. Every ‚Ä¶

Incredible experience and unbelievable service.
I reserved a seat for my friends on their honeymoon and Farhanah was incredible in looking after me and then I'm told the food service, drinks and views were exceptional and from my experience in organising it from afar it was seamless.
Hugely appreciated and the real tree for my friends

Great dining experience.
Tried the signature home made pasta. Named as Risotto Ai Funghi E Profumo Di Tartufo. ‚Ä¶

business_name: PastaMania ‚Äì Italian Casual Dining @ West Mall
text: Nice food and good vibes! Though the size of the 3 cheese sticks (already ate one before taking the photo) looks a little pitiful, would be better if there was more sticks or a bigger size. Was not too crowded when I went.
Nice hidden gem, food quality is as others shared, above average.  Friendly and attentive service.  Good place to catch a beautiful countryside sunset from the carpark.
One of the best biryani I had ever tasted. Portion is good enough for 2 pax. Price is reasonable, service is friendly and accommodating. They seriously deserve more attention.

I was not aware of any Sri Lankan restaurant until I was introduced to Kotuwa.

The food was uniquely tasty with a unique flavour different from the usual you find in Indian cuisine. The service crew was friendly and attentive throughout.

There's also an outdoor seating area, both in front of the restaurant and at the back.

We had a wonderful dining experience at Estate. Special thanks to Pauline Ng and Hui Ting for their warm and attentive service ‚Äî they truly made us feel welcomed and well taken care of throughout the meal. The food was absolutely ‚Ä¶
Great food. The sashimi is very value for money as the cuts are very thick. Tempura is crispy, yums. ‚Ä¶
We had friends over for dinner and ordered the Chili Crab Burger with Tofu Fries. Everyone was very impressed with their meal. A great variation on a classic Singapore flavour.

Amazing experience at Chimichanga Holland Village! The food was delicious, the atmosphere was vibrant. A special shoutout to Liam for his warm and attentive hospitality.. he really made us feel welcome and taken care of throughout the night. It‚Äôs always nice to be served by someone who genuinely enjoys what they do. Highly recommend this place for great Mexican food and an even better experience. Will definitely be back! üòÑ

Sunday lunch. All 3 starters we had were good - pharma ham with salad, soup of the day (potato and leek) and liver pate.

Mains : ravioli, duck spaghetti, chicken and fish of the day. All nicely done.

Finished the meal off with lemon tart, very refreshing!
Standard bar food, but it is DEFINITELY a ‚Äú Hideaway‚Äù to chill in!

Delish steak, curry chicken in a chill place.

First time, and definitely not the last. Ordered the meat platter for 2-3. Loved the caramelized steak! Super umami, with natural flavour, enhanced by the peppers and salt. Very well executed in medium, such that it's still tender and raw enough, without being too dry. The sausage was crunchy and tasty. A tad of a let down was the lamb. The taste is good, without being overly gamey, but done in medium made it a bit tough. The cuts selected for the price point is not my source of complaint. I'll probably make it a medium rare the next time round.

Another hit is the Mummy's Curry Chicken. It comes with 4 drumsticks, and 6 to 7 huge soft brastagi potatoes, chilling in a thick, spicy, delish, yet not overly hot gravy. Yums! We mopped it all up with the baguette.

The 4 seasons thin crust pizza was also another hit. A 10 inch size that comes in 4 flavours. I managed only to grab the ham and turkey slice, before it was cleared by my other hungry kakis, and that was good! Many agree that the mushroom slice is yums! Generous with the proteins and cheese. Ingredients were fresh and made for a good starter.

The fried chicken cutlet with waffle was decently good, but was overshadowed by the other 3 mains.

The drinks menu is also very extensive, both for non and alcoholic types.

Service is welcoming and the atmosphere is so chill and relaxed! Great place to chat and chill with the family.

Will be back again! üôÇ

We came on Saturday and ordered the tasting menu. The food is great with excellent service! The degustation set lunch is $98 per person and it‚Äôs quite affordable especially the number of dishes and quality. Highly recommended place
Ambience cosy, service staffs very courtesy, friendly and pleasant. Food extremely good, tasty and delicious too. Give it a thump up

Restaurant Labyrinth is highlighting the Singaporean cuisine in a brand new way. Chef Han and his team creates the most stunning dishes when recreating the local street food and I have discovered so many new dishes here! Every dish has a ‚Ä¶
Had a great meal here with my girlfriends ‚Äî the Peranakan dishes were super flavourful and authentic. Service was warm and attentive too. Highly recommend!
